https://www.opentlc.com/labs/ocp4_advanced_deployment/06_1_Machine_Management_Solution_Lab.html#_move_the_router_to_the_newly_created_infranode

oc project openshift-machine-api
oc get machineset
oc get machineset pg13-wvrz8-worker-us-east-2a -o yaml

spec:
      metadata:
        labels:
          node-role.kubernetes.io/infra: ""
          infra: "infra"



change name as well as cluster-api-machine set (use infra instead of worker)

Get rid of status 

oc get machineset pg13-wvrz8-worker-us-east-2a -o yaml > MachineSet-Original.yaml

diff MachineSet.yaml MachineSet-Original.yaml 

move router oc patch clusteringress default -n openshift-ingress-operator --type=merge --patch='{"spec":{"nodePlacement":{"nodeSelector": {"matchLabels":{"node-role.kubernetes.io/infra":""}}}}}' 

# delete the router deployment as a workaround to the operator not working 100%
oc delete deployment router-default -n openshift-ingress


oc patch clusteringress default -n openshift-ingress-operator --type=merge --patch='{"spec":{"replicas": 1}}'
